Objects: objects are stored in the form of key-value pairs 

we can create object like this,

let obj = {
    name: "Alice",
    age: 30,
    city: "New York"
}


console.log("Object:", obj); // logs the whole object
console.log("Name:", obj.name); // logs the name attribute and  value
console.log("Age:", obj.age); //logs age 
console.log("City:", obj.city); // log city 

